'''伊度亞度·捷西斯·華加斯·羅哈斯'''（{{lang-es|'''Eduardo Jesús Vargas Rojas'''}}，{{IPA-es|eˈðwarðo ˈβaɾɣas}}；{{bd|1989年|11月20日|catIdx=Vargas Rojas}}）是一名[[智利|智利]][[足球員|足球員]]，司職[[前鋒|前鋒]]，亦可擔任中場邊路工作，現時效力[[巴西足球甲級聯賽|巴西足球甲級聯賽]]球隊[[米内罗竞技俱乐部|米内罗]]。

==俱樂部生涯==
<!--
{{TransH}}
巴尔加斯最早在[[倫卡|倫卡]]的業餘劇樂部踢球,因為家住得離[[圣地亚哥_(智利|圣地亚哥)]]的大俱樂部遠，他沒有加入任何的青年隊,直到2006年，他在第三級別的業餘聯賽踢球時候，他參加了一項在[[蒙特港|蒙特港]]舉行的錦標賽，當時他是隊內的頭號得分手。

不久之後,{{Tsl|en|Osvaldo Hurtado (footballer)|奧斯瓦爾多·烏爾塔多(智利足球運動員)|奧斯瓦爾多·烏爾塔多}} [[Osvaldo_Hurtado_(footballer)|Osvaldo Hurtado]] contacted Vargas with [[Jorge_Aravena|Jorge Aravena]] (In this moment coach of [[Cobreloa|Cobreloa]]), where he was submitted to several evaluations. Finally he was incorporated to Cobreloa squad in 2006.

He participated in Cobreloa B, third Division team, scoring with the team, against [[Universidad_Arturo_Prat|Universidad Arturo Prat]] on 7 August 2006, after he scored another goal against [[San_Marcos_de_Arica|San Marcos de Arica]] on 28 August 2006.
{{TransF}}
===智利大學城Universidad de Chile===
{{TransH}}
In January 2010, [[Club_Universidad_de_Chile|Club Universidad de Chile]] signed the winger from [[Cobreloa|Cobreloa]] for around $700.000. His high caliber performances in the [[2011_Chilean_Primera_División_season|Chilean Championship]] and the [[2011_Copa_Sudamericana|2011 Copa Sudamericana]] have piqued the interest of several prominent European clubs, including [[F.C._Internazionale_Milano|Internazionale]] with manager [[Claudio_Ranieri|Claudio Ranieri]] recently alluding to a January move for the forward.

In November 2011, he was chosen as a candidate for [[South_American_Footballer_of_the_Year|South American Footballer of the Year]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2011/11/656-407381-9-eduardo-vargas-pelea-con-neymar-para-ser-el-mejor-de-america.shtml|title=Eduardo Vargas pelea con Neymar para ser el mejor de América |work=latercera.com |accessdate=25 November 2011|language=es}}</ref>(finally, was only defeated by [[Neymar|Neymar]], and got the second position), and in December he was chosen [[Chilean_Footballer_of_the_Year|Chilean Footballer of the Year 2011]].

Eduardo Vargas scored twice in the Final of the [[2011_Copa_Sudamericana|2011 Copa Sudamericana]]. He scored in the third minute and in the 87th. His two goals helped "La U" achieve its first international title, and he was elected the best player of the tournament. Also, Vargas is the top scorer of the [[Copa_Sudamericana|Copa Sudamericana]]'s history with 11 goals.
{{TrasnF}}
===拿坡里===
{{transH}}
[[S.S.C._Napoli|Napoli]] finally purchased the player's services for around $17.9 million (£11.5 million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nesn.com/2011/12/eduardo-vargas-signs-with-napoli-snubs-move-to-english-premier-league.html|title=Eduardo Vargas Signs With Napoli, Snubs Move to English Premier League |work=NESN.com |accessdate=19 December 2011}}</ref>On 23 December 2011, [[S.S.C._Napoli|S.S.C. Napoli]] President [[Aurelio_De_Laurentiis|Aurelio De Laurentiis]], announced that Vargas would finally arrive at the club. "I would like to inform you officially that we purchased Vargas, a few minutes ago I received a call from Dr. De Nicola, who visited the footballer and gave his ok under medical and athletic profile. We signed the contract and we also won the competition by strong Club who wanted the player. This is the testimony that our observatory is always open and we are continuously looking for young talents in the world that can make the case of Napoli and for the growth of our team".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1000667/napoli-president-announces-eduardo-vargas-signing?cc=5901|publisher=ESPN FC|title=Napoli Announce Vargas Signing|date=23 December 2011|accessdate=2011-12-23}}</ref>Vargas arrived at Napoli on 6 January 2012 and signed on 9 January.<ref>[http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2012/01/09/520760/eduardo-vargas-en-su-presentacion-en-napoli-me-da-gusto-que-me-comparen-con-sanchez.html Eduardo Vargas en su presentación en Napoli: "Me da gusto que me comparen con Sánchez" (in Spanish)]</ref>
On 20 September 2012, the first match of Napoli's [[Europa_League|Europa League]] campaign, Vargas scored three goals in a 4-0 victory against [[AIK_Fotboll|AIK Fotboll]]. This was the first time that a Chilean player scored a [[hat-trick|hat-trick]] in a continental competition in Europe.
{{TrasnF}}
===Grêmio===
{{Transh}}
On 17 January 2013, Vargas agreed to go on loan to Brazilian side [[Grêmio_Foot-Ball_Porto_Alegrense|Grêmio]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gremio.net/news/view.aspx?id=15625&language=0&news_type_id=4|publisher=Portal Oficial do Grêmio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|title=Eduardo Vargas em Porto Alegre|date=17 January 2013|accessdate=2013-01-17}}</ref>He made his first appearance six days later in a [[Copa_Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]] match against [[Ecuadorian|Ecuadorian]] side [[LDU_Quito|LDU Quito]]. He scored his first goal on February 21 against [[Fluminense_FC|Fluminense]] in the [[Copa_Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]]. On March 31, he scored his first goal in the [[Campeonato_Gaúcho|Campeonato Gaúcho]], converting a penalty at the [[Arena_do_Grêmio|Arena do Grêmio]]. The game finished 1-1.
{{TransF}}
